Jace Bell, a senior undergraduate student majoring in Environmental Science and Biology at the University of Northern Iowa, reached out to James Rising expressing interest in his research and inquiring about working under his mentorship at the University of Delaware. Jace's specific interest lies in James's research on the economic impacts of climate change and integrated water systems, aligning with their aspiration to pursue the M.S. Water Science & Policy program at UD. They also mentioned their background in water quality research and hydrologic management. James's response acknowledges Jace's interests and suggests considering the Environmental Science & Management (ESM) program with a Marine track or the Ph.D. program in Marine Policy. James emphasizes limited funding availability and encourages Jace to apply by the end of the year, mentioning their interest in James's research in their statement of purpose. The response also offers further assistance if needed.
